    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single below-required factor (Test conditions, Gradation 1 vs. required 2) is accepted given the deterministic quasi-static COU and the regulatory standing of ASTM F1717 as the standard protocol. All QoI comparisons satisfy E/uval < 1.96 and <10% absolute difference. The Batch 2024-Q3 material dataset (dataVintage 2025-02-21) predates the model revision of 2025-03-17 by 24 days; the team assessed the contact stiffness penalty factor update as not material to bulk material property inputs and accepted the dataset without formal re-validation against the revised model build. Overall credibility sufficient to support regulatory submission for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw design.",
